==English==

===Etymology===
[[sweet]] + [[fish]]
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-irreg|sweetfish}}

# An [[amphidromous]] fish, the ''[[ayu]]'' of East Asia, the only member of its [[genus]], ''Plecoglossus altivelis'', family ''Plecoglossidae'', named and prized for its sweet tasting flesh, especially in [[Japan]]. It is a game fish and is also subject to extensive [[aquaculture]].

====Translations====
*Japanese: [[アユ]] ([[鮎]], [[あゆ]], ayu)

